  "body": "When running `NewSimulatedBackend` for testing, resources are not freed\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nany system\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNo memory leak\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nMemory is not freed\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun `NewSimulatedBackend` and observe memory (pprof image attached)\r\n\r\nThe problem is that the `SimulatedBackend` does not offer a `Close` method to do a proper clean up. The issue arises at `state.NewDatabaseWithCache`, which allocates a cache via `trie.NewDatabaseWithCache`, which can not be closed due to missing cleanup function.\r\n\r\n![pprof002](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/88287/63557152-2ce59180-c50d-11e9-9163-1d3cc1cd2f19.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nthanks @janos for the actual investigation\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
